<p id="p19">This time, it&rsquo;s the Emmy-award-winning writer David X. Cohen. David started writing on Beavis and Butthead in the early &lsquo;90s before joining The Simpsons, where he was responsible for many well-known episodes like Lisa the Vegetarian, The Itchy and Scratchy and Poochie Show, and Homer3. Then, in 1999, with Simpsons creator Matt Groening, David co-developed Futurama, which recently dropped its 13th season on Hulu and Disney+.</p>
<p id="p20">But David&rsquo;s history is not just in television. He worked in the robotics lab while attending Harvard, studied theoretical computer science, and has a deep history with technology all the way back to the early days of home computers. As you can expect, there was a lot for us to talk about.</p>
